                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.00/2905: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">Then in France</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-09-01T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 1, 1936—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>B–15. Your 79, August 29, 3 p.m., and your 83, August 31, 4 p.m.<note n="64"
                        xml:id="d458fn64">Latter not printed.</note> In a separate telegram I have
                    requested you to telegraph the text of the recommendations of the diplomatic
                    corps to render more humane the conflict in Spain. In your reply please let us
                    know whether there has been any change in the procedure set forth in your 79 of
                    August 29, 3 p.m., whereby the Spanish Government would be consulted as to
                    whether it has any objection to the submission of the same proposal to the rebel
                    leaders.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
